{
  "name": "Diverticulitis",
  "remarks": [
    "Acute diverticulitis becomes common after age 50 and rises steadily with age; roughly 18% of people develop at least one episode over a lifetime, most commonly presenting in the 6th-7th decade of life.",
    "About 75-80% of episodes are uncomplicated and managed with oral antibiotics/bowel rest, while 20-25% are complicated by abscess or perforation and require IV antibiotics, drainage, or surgery.",
    "Sources: Tursi A. et al., 'Diverticulosis and diverticular disease: an update...' World J Gastroenterol 2015; Feuerstein JD & Falchuk KR, 'Diverticulitis', Mayo Clin Proc 2016."
  ],
  "states": {
